{"parentUuid":"03950570-3c56-4e7d-909e-1d24607c8a13","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"0d0af761-1c1a-49e9-a1e6-a7a160c700bf","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The encoding issue is causing garbled output. The PowerShell console is using GB2312/GBK encoding on this Windows system, but the script is UTF-8 without BOM. Also, the DISM command requires elevation too.\n\nThe main problem here is: I need admin rights to do most of the Copilot removal. I can't get that through this terminal.\n\nLet me take a different approach: write a proper .ps1 script that the user can right-click and \"Run as Administrator\", or I can try to use `Start-Process -Verb RunAs` to self-elevate the script.\n\nActually, the core issue is:\n1. I'm running in a bash shell on Windows through the Claude Code harness\n2. To remove system apps, I need admin rights\n3. Getting admin rights through this path is difficult\n\nWhat I should do is write a comprehensive removal script that the user can run themselves as admin. Or I can try using `Start-Process powershell -Verb RunAs` which will pop up a UAC prompt for the user.\n\nLet me create a proper admin-elevated script that:\n1. Self-elevates\n2. Finds and removes Copilot\n3. Uses the right encoding (UTF-8 with BOM for PowerShell on Windows)\n\nLet me write the file with BOM encoding.","signature":"0d0af761-1c1a-49e9-a1e6-a7a160c700bf"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":576,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":37120,"output_tokens":1657,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"stop_details":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"e0371597-1106-46be-90b0-691cf6734f00","timestamp":"2026-05-18T17:07:43.179Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"clau